2. d4 Nf6 3. Bd3 e5 4. c3 Be7 5. Nf3 Nbd7 6. O-O O-O 7. Bc2 $5 {We have
already discussed this interesting idea. First of all, this is a prophylactic
against ...d6-d5. At the same time, White can always consider the option of
Bb3.} c6 8. Nbd2 Qc7 9. Re1 Rd8 10. Nf1 {As always, White is happy to play Ruy
Lopez with extra tempis. The knight is heading for g3.} Nf8 11. Ng3 Ng6 {
This move secures the safety of the black king. On the downside, the white
knight has now access to the important f5-square.} ({In case of} 11... Bg4 {
