1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Bd3 e5 4. c3 Nbd7 ({The more common move order is} 4...
Be7 5. Nf3 Nbd7 6. O-O) 5. Nf3 {In most cases, this move will take us
to the main lines. We should know, however, that Black has now the additional
option of 5...d5} ({Even more precise would have been} 5. f4 $1 Be7 6. Ne2 $1 {
with very good attacking prospects. It's important to remember that the knight
belongs exactly to e2. In case of 6.Nf3, Black can consider 6...d5.}) 5... Be7
{After this move, White can go for his usual setup.} ({After} 5... d5 $5 6. Qe2
$1 {White still keeps a slight advantage.}) 6. O-O O-O 7. Nbd2 c6 8. Re1 Re8 9.
Nf1 Bf8 10. Ng3 {This is the Ruy Lopez way of handling the position.} ({
Being a Torre player, however, I would prefer} 10. Bg5 $1 {Let's take a look
at an example.} h6 11. Bh4 g6 {This is played with the idea of ...Bg7.} ({
In my opinion, the more reliable is} 11... Be7) 12. N1d2 $3 {With this move, White
enters a favourable version of Torre. Against the Torre setup, the move ...
c7-c6 does not work very well. The c6-pawn will be very useful against setups
based on Nc3. Now, White is going to install a knight on c4.} Bg7 13. Bf1 $3
Qc7 14. Nc4 {The black centre is under pressure.} {It's important to know that}
exd4 (14... b5 15. dxe5 dxe5 16. Qd6 Qxd6 17. Nxd6 $16 {[%cal Ga2a4]}) {
is well met by} 15. Bg3 $3 $16 {with a huge advantage for White.}) 10... g6 11.
h3 Qc7 12. Bg5 $1 {[%cal Gd1d2]} Bg7 $6 {This move is a serious mistake since
White can execute his positional idea - Qd2.} ({Nevertheless, even after} 12...
h6 13. Be3 Bg7 14. Qd2 $14 {White retains his advantage.}) 13. Qd2 $1 b5 {
We know that this move is almost always premature in this pawn structure.} 14.
Bh6 {Since this is a blitz game, White prefers to handle the position in a
more aggressive way.} ({More thematic would have been} 14. a4 $1 $18 Rb8 15.
axb5 cxb5 16. Bh6 {with a huge advantage for White.}) 14... Nf8 15. Bxg7 Kxg7
16. Rac1 $16 a5 17. c4 b4 18. c5 $1 exd4 19. cxd6 Qb6 20. e5 Nd5 21. Be4 Ne6
22. Bxd5 cxd5 23. Ne2 Ba6 24. Nexd4 Rac8 25. d7 1-0

