{[%evp 0,54,28,50,79,60,62,34,24,8,45,49,58,62,42,29,30,29,60,47,47,30,88,94,
64,54,81,58,65,59,99,99,70,57,40,-18,15,-58,-77,-104,-117,-117,-128,-91,-114,
-114,-138,-138,-64,-140,-148,-308,-386,-1086,-1158,-1191,-1196] Now, we shall
take a look at two games by GM Bologan who advocates the setup based on Be3.} 
1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Bd3 e5 4. c3 g6 5. Nf3 Nbd7 6. O-O Bg7 7. Be3 {This is
Bologan's favourite idea.} ({My preferred way of handling the position is} 7.
Re1 O-O 8. Bg5 {reaching a Torre territory.}) 7... O-O 8. Nbd2 {So far, White
does not feel the need to include h2-h3 because the move ...Ng4 can be met by
Bg5.} Re8 9. Re1 h6 {[%cal Gf6g4] Now, when the g5-square is under control
Black is ready to play ...Ng4. Therefore, White should play} 10. h3 Kh7 11. Qc2
{Obviously, White enjoys a small advantage because Black cannot easily put
pressure on the centre.} b6 12. a4 {[%cal Ga4a5] A thematic idea in this kind
of position. Black should reckon with the advance a4-a5.} a6 $1 {This is the
best choice. The idea is to answer a4-a5 with ...b6-b5.} ({Note that the
advance} 12... a5 $2 {should never be played. Now, the c4-square becomes a
stronghold for White's minor pieces. Additionally, the move ...a7-a5 weakens
all the light squares on the queenside.}) 13. b4 {White keeps gaining space on
the queenside. This is his main strategy in such positions.} Bb7 14. a5 {
I find this advance a bit premature. Of course, such inaccuracy is quite
normal for a blitz game.} ({When the bishop has been already committed to b7,
White can play} 14. d5 {A possible follow up would be} c6 15. c4 a5 16. bxa5
Rxa5 17. Nb3 Ra8 18. Nfd2 {when White has a very promising play on the queenside.
}) ({Switching to Torre type of play after} 14. dxe5 {is quite reasonable as
well.}) 14... exd4 15. cxd4 b5 16. Rac1 Rc8 $132 {[%cal Gc7c5] Black managed
to obtain decent counterplay because the break ...c7-c5 is already on the
agenda.} 17. Bf4 c5 18. Bxd6 c4 19. Bf1 c3 20. Nb3 Bxe4 21. Qd1 c2 22. Qd2 Bxf3
23. gxf3 Rxe1 24. Qxe1 Nd5 25. Nc5 Nxc5 26. Bxc5 Qg5+ 27. Kh1 Re8 0-1

