9. Qc2 O-O 10. Bg5 Be6 11. Nd2 {[%cal Gd3c4] White has a slightly more
pleasant position. He can consider exchanging the light-squared bishops via c4.
}) 7... O-O 8. Nbd2 Re8 ({Of course, White is not afraid of} 8... Ng4 {in view
of} 9. Bg5 f6 10. Bh4 {with a better position.}) 9. Re1 Bg4 10. h3 $2 {This
move gives Black enough counterplay.} ({White should have played} 10. d5 Ne7
11. c4 a5 12. c5 {with a fantastic version of the KID.}) 10... exd4 11. cxd4
