1. d4 d6 2. e4 $1 Nf6 3. Bd3 $1 e5 4. c3 d5 $1 {In the whole line with 3.Bd3,
this is possibly the best position that Black can choose. However, not many
people know it, and even fewer people have analyzed it deeply! This position
was considered good for Black years ago, but the engines changed everything.}
5. dxe5 Nxe4 (5... dxe4 $2 {SUPER SOS !!! I MUST KNOW THIS VERY WELL!!} 6. Bb5+
$3 {This is the engines discoverey} c6 {leads to a better endgame for White} (
6... Bd7 7. Bc4 $1 $16 (7. Qb3 $1 $16 {is also possible} c6 8. Bc4 Nd5 9. Ne2
$1 $16 Na6 10. Bxa6 bxa6 11. O-O e3 12. fxe3 $3 Bc5 13. c4 $16) 7... Ng4 8.
Bxf7+ $3 Kxf7 9. e6+ Kxe6 10. Qxg4+ Kf7 11. Qh5+ (11. Qxe4 $16 {Black will
exchange queens and will have some compensation for the pawn.}) 11... g6 (11...
Kg8 12. Qd5+ Be6 13. Qxe6#) 12. Qd5+ Kg7 13. Be3 $16) (6... Nfd7 $2 {is losing
on a spot} 7. e6 fxe6 8. Qh5+ g6 9. Qe5 $18) 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. exf6 cxb5 9. Bg5
$1 Kc7 (9... g6 10. Nd2 Bf5 11. Ne2 $18) 10. Nd2 gxf6 (10... Bf5 11. Ne2 $16)
11. Bf4+ Kb6 12. Nxe4 $16) 6. Nf3 {SUPER SUPER SOS !!!! In the lines that
follow, we do not have to memorize everything! We just get a good feeling
about the arising positions! A VERY IMPORTANT RULE NOW !! : Whenever i see the
move 1...Ne4-c5, all moves are possible ..depending on the situation: 2.Bc2, 2.
Be2 , 2.Bb5! (this is usually the best when there's a knight on c6!) ...and
sometimes, its also very good to leave my bishop on d3 to be captured by the
knight!   SUPER SOS: MY NEXT MOVES WILL BE EITHER 7. 0-0 , or 7 .Nbd2 first ...
with typical play! We are creating a threat now: Bxe4, followed by Qxd8 and Ng5
} ({it is wrong to grab the pawn after:} 6. Bxe4 $2 {it is wrong to capture
the pawn after:} dxe4 7. Qa4+ Bd7 8. Qxe4 Bc6 9. Qg4 h5) 6... Nc5 $5 {Is the
recent try and a severe move} (6... Nc6 $6 {The most popular move, everybody
puts the knight on c6, but this is not generally a good idea because it leaves
the d5 pawn very weak!} 7. Nbd2 $1 {I prefer this move} (7. O-O $1 $14 {
and now...some sample lines...I don't believe you should memorize much!} Bg4 (
7... Nc5 8. Bb5 $1 {sos !! after an Nc5 move, whenever this Bb5 pin is
available.. it is usually good} Bg4 9. h3 Bh5 10. Re1 (10. b4 $3 Ne6 11. Qa4
Qd7 (11... Bxf3 12. Bxc6+ bxc6 13. Qxc6+ Ke7 14. gxf3 g6 15. Rd1) 12. Nd4 Nexd4
13. cxd4 a6 14. f4 f5 (14... Rb8 15. Bxc6 bxc6 16. Qxa6) 15. a3 Rb8 16. Bxc6
Qxc6 (16... bxc6 17. Qxa6) 17. Qxc6+ bxc6 18. Nc3 Kd7 19. Re1 Ke6 20. Bd2 Be7
21. Rac1 Be8 22. Na4 $18) 10... Be7 11. g4 Bg6 12. Nd4 O-O 13. Bxc6 bxc6 14.
Nxc6 Qe8 15. Qxd5 Nd3 16. Rd1 Bh4 17. f4 $16) 8. Nbd2 Nc5 (8... Be7 $2 {
is losing due to} 9. Nxe4 dxe4 10. Bxe4 Qxd1 11. Rxd1 Nxe5 12. Bxb7 Bxf3 13.
gxf3 Rb8 14. Be4 $18) (8... Nxe5 $2 9. Nxe4 dxe4 $2 (9... Bxf3 10. gxf3 dxe4
11. Bxe4 Qxd1 12. Rxd1 c6 13. Bf4 f6 14. b4 $16 Rd8 15. Be3 (15. a4 $18) 15...
